<br>
That right there will totally and completely destroy camping in SWG. The level mill will not exist in SWG the way you interpret it.<br>
<br>
In SWG, you can gain levels simply by interacting with the environment you choose to be a part of. It's not all about combat. There are already tons of people on the SWG boards who intend to play BUT NEVER INTEND TO FIGHT. These people will be the traders, merchants, politicians, and craftsmen of SWG. But levels in and of themselves are not relevant to SWG, except that they give you more skill points to spend. A person's level is only indicative of how many skill points he has earned, but it is NOT indicative of where he spent them. In SWG, you will be able to, literally, be a level &quot;x&quot; hairdresser. Seriously. Also, your character's &quot;hit points&quot; will never significantly raise - standing still, anyone is easy to kill. But a player with lots of combat SKILLS will be survivable, while the level 15 lounge singer will not be. Theoretically, then, a competant &quot;low level&quot; player will be able to smoke an eBayed &quot;high level&quot; character. This is all in the FAQ.<br>
<br>
Now, whether or not SWG pulls this off is anyone's guess. But you have to admit what they claim to be doing is setting the EQ model on it's ear - it's destroying the EQ model of level/loot/repeat. Instead, you have what could become a community of artisans, traders, rebels and Imperials.<br>
<br>
Xaen, in all honesty - and please don't take this as patronizing - but I think you should read the FAQ. You seem to be under the impression that SWG is going to be &quot;EverQuest 2.&quot; To get a sense of exactly how revolutionary this game  is, you need to understand what they plan to do with it. No offense, bud, but you're arguing from a position of ignorant indifference. If you're interested enough to play &quot;Devil's Advocate,&quot; then please, read the FAQ and argue in an informed way.<br>
<br>
And finally, some comments I have to refute:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Yes, i do think EQ's spawn system is good as any games going to get. This doesn't mean I like it. It just means that there isn't any way that is feasable to make it more enjoyable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I challenge this notion. As technology and innovation march on, we will see better and more innovative games. Almost every game coming out since EQ has a better system than EQ, or has at least tried to offer a better system. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> To claim that mobs are all random, so that means no one can &quot;camp&quot; would be a bit off. As long as there is a single point of interest (A dungeon, for a quest, etc, which SWG claims it will have plenty of), there will be a reason for people to go there. This in itself will be the &quot;camp&quot;. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->As explained by Holocron in my first post, these things WILL NOT EXIST until the player in question encounters them. At that point it will be up to him how he wants to approach that point of interest. Does he have good combat skills? Maybe he'll attack. Does he have good diplomatic skills? Maybe he'll walk up and introduce himself. Does he have good tradeskills? Maybe he'll offer a trade, make some credits, and leave. Also, these POIs won't last forever. Once you have discovered them and interacted with them (or avoided them), they will quickly disappear. Then when someone else comes by, a similiar but different POI will present itself to THAT person and he will also choose to interact with it or avoid it. And that is why camping won't happen. Shit doesn't respawn. Once it's dead - it's dead. Gone. Fini. You'll have to move on if you want to encounter any more creatures.<br>
<br>
Therefore, no camping, KSing is obsolete, and level/loot/repeat does not exist. <br>
<br>
Of course, SWG will no doubt have it's own problems as thousands of gamers find new exploits and whatnot, but the problems of EverQuest will not be problems in SWG.<br>
<br>
